    {
      "id": "step-3-core-architecture",
      "title": "Core Architecture Layers",
      "description": "ArtifactFS is organized into three cooperating areas. The orchestration layer owns the daemon lifecycle and the registry of mounted repositories. The filesystem layer presents those repositories to the operating system and captures local writes. The git and hydration layer is the source of truth — it stores commits and streams blobs into view on demand.",
